This world was never good enough for someone as beautiful as you. I will miss you with an aching longing, a missing piece of me.
Dana had a dysfunctional childhood, which led her to live with our older sister the last year of her life. She thrived, flourished, reached all her goals with a vigor for life, when she needed transportation to her jobs which were only 6 minutes away from her house and a car wasn’t financially feasible, a motorcycle was the next best option. Living in a quiet rural, rarely trafficked area, it wasn’t a cause for concern. She was so careful, responsible, did everything right, only riding to and from her job which was only 6 minutes away. And even then, a tragedy occurred. WATCH OUT FOR OUR FELLOW BIKERS, please GET OFF YOUR PHONES. So many tragedies can be prevented if we just watched out for one another.
Please share and/or donate to her gofundme (link in my bio) which will cover her funeral costs and possibly her medical bills. https://gofund.me/80ad9c99
Please no insensitive messages, let our family mourn.
I’ll always love you my little firecracker, my supernova, my now celestial being💜

We laid our little sister to rest yesterday on a beautiful sunny day, under cascading willow trees, embellished with Spanish moss. Nature welcomed her with bird songs and dancing trees. The community of bikers that welcomed her with open arms had a ride out in her honor, sounds I never thought would induce so much heartache and aching pain. What I would give to have her back, to hear her infectious laugh at least once more. I’ll love you always💜
Please consider sharing and/or donating towards her funeral cost & possibly medical bills (link in my bio). Thank you amigas💜

Save a life, look twice💜I just wanted to say thank you so so so much to every single person who has donated and/or shared. I’m beyond grateful for you amigas💜 thank you for being such an amazing community. And while I can’t get to every single message, please know that each message has touched my heart and is seen💜
please continue to share!

This is NOT permissive parenting. Boundaries are firmly held while simultaneously holding space and empathy for their big emotions. Understanding that their brains aren’t physiologically capable of a lot of life skills that are mastered later on. Impulse control- around 4 years old, sharing- 5/6 years old, independent emotional regulation-5/6 years old. It is telling my toddler “no”, firmly holding that boundary while allowing them to feel angry/sad and helping them regulate their emotions by remaining calm myself. Not sending them away or isolating them when they’re experiencing big emotions, but rather coregulate with them & model emotional maturity.
 It is letting them make mistakes, and not instill fear of making them, not screaming or punishing when a mistake is made; because that would only result in an adult who is scared to do anything because they’re scared to make mistakes.
 It’s raising emotionally intelligent children.

#consciousparenting #respectfulparenting #gentleparenting #generationaltrauma #generationaltraumahealing #childhoodtrauma #childhoodtraumarecovery #howtoraiseemotionallyintelligentchildren #emotionalintelligence #raisingemotionallyintelligentchildren
